  "prompt": "Who was the Guru of Guru Nanak Dev Ji?",
  "response": "Guru Nanak Dev Ji, the founder of Sikhism, is regarded as the primary Guru in Sikh tradition and is often considered to have received spiritual enlightenment directly from God rather than having a human Guru or teacher. Sikhism teaches that Guru Nanak Dev Ji attained divine wisdom and understanding through his own spiritual experiences and communion with the Divine. Therefore, he did not have a human Guru in the way that his successors in the line of Sikh Gurus did.",
